inn1.comm: Roach starts on off stump with an angled ball from wide of the crease, about good length, Rohit defends carefully
Rohit takes a big stride out and blocks a pitched up delivery
another appreciable forward movement and he guides a fullish ball watchfully to cover, no movement so far for Roach though
diving stop at extra cover, Rohit has got the front foot easing into the shot nicely but he's not gone hard at the ball and the fielder is able to cut it off

uh oh, Rohit runs into trouble, almost, pushes down the ground, mid off dives, Rohit takes a few steps out, stops, takes a few more steps, Dhawan is ball watching, and Rohit makes it back in time as the throw goes to the keeper
across to defend a back of a length ball, no swing, no seam, so far
short is the length first up to Dhawan, 138.2 kph already from Tino, Dhawan cramped for room, and stabs it away
short once more, but leg-sidish, and Dhawan gets India going with a tuck to fine leg, and Tino contributes with a front-foot no-ball
Rohit backs away to leg and gives the free hit everything, but it is dug in rather too short, and he misses, free hit still on

whoa, little Bravo is confused, he's taken the catch off a sliced slog at third man, and begun celebrating, he's even kicked the ball away, before he spots a furious Pollard shouting 'Bravo, Bravo', pointing to his head, imploring his fielder to use his brains and gesticulating for him to throw the ball back, Bravo has a sheepish smile on now, Sammy walks up to him and collapses with a burst of laughter into a hug
length ball around off played out to covers from the crease
bouncer to Dhawan, and he pulls it off around chest height to the deep square leg boundary
this is a high full toss around off but Dhawan has guided it straight to cover
Roach in a theatrical appeal for lbw but it is turned down, this length ball appeared to do too much with the angle he creates
pitched up, driven firmly but mid off gets to it
on the front foot to defend
whipped away, Roach overdoes the angle and the length, and Rohit takes his for runs past square leg
that is put away, overpitched again, slight width and Dhawan is up to to thread it between extra cover and mid off with an eager followthrough
now Dhawan coming forward confidently on the front foot and guiding a length ball to cover
back of a length, not much room, pushed to point

hello, where did that come from, Rohit was looking to leave a pacy back of a length ball, it was the right call on the original line outside off, but it then changed direction alarmingly, snaked in, bounced, pinged the glove, not sure Sammy at gully realised that, didn't make an extra effort to go for the take, got to it on the bounce
some response from Rohit, Tino pounds it in, short outside off, Rohit winds up and sends it soaring over the third man rope
length ball played out to the leg side
pitched up now from Tino, Rohit calmly pushes it down to mid off
moving forward smoothly to push a length delivery to mid off

smart work from Roach, Dhawan skipped out and went through with a straight push in the air to a good length ball, but he didn't get it far from Roach, who stuck out his right hand, it popped in the air further to the bowler's right, but he recovered quickly to take it
back of a length into the batsman from wide of the crease, defended
left alone outside off stump
short of a length again, Kohli happy to block
takes a big stride out and lets a good length ball go through outside off
spears a good length ball down the leg side, at 143.4 kph, rolls away off the pad
banged in short now, quick but offering width and Kohli's upper cut it over the deep backward point boundary, and it is another no-ball
Kohli swings at the free hit, a length ball around off, hits it over the bowler but has found no timing
overpitched, but Rohit, as he has been doing today, does not go hard at it, caresses it to wide mid off
and again, fullish delivery, around off stump, Rohit is forward to pat it back
leaves a straight good length ball a few feet outside off
right forward again, Best gets this to climb at 138 kph from just short of driving length, but Rohit is in position to defend without bother
Roach on middle and leg with that angle, Kohli tucks the length ball straight to square leg
presses forward to defend a length ball outside off, no movement, either in air or off the pitch
a hint of movement on this one, just a hint of straightening from a good length, Kohli pushes a long way outside off, but the thin edge does not carry to the keeper
turned off the pad to fine leg
Rohit is letting go of potential scoring opportunities, not attacking as he often does, here he eases this full delivery softly past the bowler, but mid off comes around
played out to point
Sammy finds some movement and bounce first ball, good length ball with a hint of inswing, loose, late decision to steer from Kohli and he misses it
and now some outswing, excellent length, would want to be a touch closer to off as Kohli flags it through
this stays a tad low, similar line, similar length, outside off, straightens after pitching, Kohli across a long way and adjusts to block
length ball, Kohli right forward, head on top, firm defensive bat, all that
another one moves away slightly, but the line still a touch far outside off, Kohli watches it go, super start from Sammy so far
he plays at it this time, comes forward and guides a length ball to backward point, not getting the single
was already forward, this back of a length ball came in and seemed to stay a shade low judging by the way Rohit jabbed it to point
chops it towards gully for a single
moves across, gets in a better position to use the incoming angle and turns it wide of mid on
sharp length ball, 137.4 kph, he plays it off the back foot, getting across and behind the line quite solidly
ending on off from a good length, Kohli half forward to push it away
some bounce from back of a length, tight line around off, guided down to third man

Gayle glorious at wide slip, what a catch, brings his big frame down to the right and plucks this thick edge one handed, Kohli went hard at this good length delivery and not surprisingly, it is that man Darren Sammy, again in the region outside off, it was angled in and swung away slightly, but rather poor stroke from Kohli, just tried to whack it away wildly
takes a step forward and allows a bouncing length ball to go outside off
another outside edge, DK stepping forward to block, on the bounce to second slip
gets it to straighten again, DK leaves
right on off stump, superb line, Karthik forward to defend
he comes forward and defends the length delivery back to the bowler
too straight, the batsman flicks it to the leg side, but straight to the man at midwicket
another delivery on the middle stump line, the batsman comes forward and drives it to mid-on this time
it's shortish on the leg stump line, but doesn't get up at all, the batsman tucks it to backward square leg for a single
gets a short ball, but this one sails over his head. He does well to duck under it well in time
back of length delivery outside off, doesn't bounce much. DK leaves it alone
length delivery outside off, straightens a touch, Rohit leaves
length delivery on off, the batsman dabs it to the off side and takes off for a quick single
another length delivery, DK comes forward and pushes it to extra cover for a single
gets good bounce from a length, Rohit defends it to point off the front foot
he waits on the back foot and carves the length delivery past point beautifully, the timing means it beats the fielder at third man easily
this one is too straight, the batsman tucks it to backward square leg for a single
he bowls it quick and he bowls it full, knee high! Rohit is surprised by it and his hand comes off the handle as he pushes it to extra cover for a single
comes forward positively and defends the length delivery right under his nose
bowls back of length on off stump, DK goes back and guides it to third man for a single
teases the batsman with a full delivery wide outside off, Rohit resists the temptation and lets it go
angled towards the off stump, Rohit comes forward and pushes it to mid-off
now he goes for a yorker, 146 kph, the batsman digs it out towards midwicket and immediately looks at the toe of his bat.
he bowls a length delivery outside off, DK lets it go through
that's not a place to bowl when the keeper is up! Sammy bowls length down the leg side and DK just has to get some bat on it, which he does
keeps it tight on off stump, DK comes forward and defends
he is keeping it on that nagging line and length outside off, DK leaves it alone
another length delivery on off, the batsman defends it to mid-on
another tight delivery on off, bounces a touch extra, DK defends towards the leg side
this came in, bounced, hit Rohit high on the pad, and rolled to point, who ran in threw, but Rohit had lumbered across by then, throw missed anyway
149.2 kph, he's been quick and quicker today, around middle stump with the incoming angle, he goes back and turns it to fine leg
length outside off now, dabbed wide of third man
width for the cut, DK cuts, finds point on the bounce

needless, absolutely needless, DK drives an overpitched delivery, Pollard at mid off dives, recovers to pick the ball up, DK is more than half way down by then, Rohit has not moved, DK turns back, Pollard fires it in to the keeper, no way DK is making it, but he dives big, and makes it
back of a length, on the pads, away to fine leg
angled in fullish to middle and leg, brings bat in front of pad to push to mid on
this bounces from a length outside off now, left alone
just outside off stump, short of driving length, excellent stuff from Sammy, played out towards point
tight line and length once more, defended to the off side
pitched up for the drive, but he cannot time it and hits it hard into the ground, and to extra cover
this should have gone, wide length ball, DK cut hard but point leaped to deny him
bouncer, 142 kph, into the batsman, who pulls out of the way
short of a length, cramps him for room, played out softly
Rohit breaks free, pitched up outside off, Rohit makes some more room with half a step to leg, and drills it high over extra cover
slower offcutter, he waits on the front foot and runs it down to third man
climbing on middle stump, he goes back and across and pushes in front of midwicket for one, India need more of rotating the strike
this is 145.5 kph alright but Best sends the length ball way down the leg side
back of a length, slower one, around off stump, softly guided behind point
starts with a big wide down the leg side
angled in fullish to off stump from wide of the crease, pushed back
opens the face and runs a length ball to point for one
this is what Pollard will do, DK was across to try and work it to leg as soon as he saw the big incoming angle from wide of the crease, but it didn't come on
overdid the angle this time, this was ending on leg stump, and Karthik nudges it fine
neat, presses forward to a pitched up ball, it rolls away in front of midwicket and they are off for one
back of a length ball turned to third man with a open face
length offspinner first up outside off, punched to long off from the crease
scurries across to another length offspinner and guides it behind point
allows an offspinner to come on and nudges it square to leg
fuller with the flighted offspinner, he goes across outside off stump and works it to leg, but finds midwicket
stretches forward to block
shortish and quick, he swivels and pulls it down to fine leg
tossed up and turning in outside off, left alone
spinning down the pads, he goes across and nudges it fine
played out with the turn to square leg
waits for this offspinner to come on and knocks it towards point
goes across in the crease and pushes to covers for a single
moves forward and nudges with the spin to midwicket, it is coming on rather slowly from the spinners
cut hard but backward point dives to his right and saves runs
spins in and hits him as he misses with the forward defensive push
96.7 kph this one, he cuts and finds backward point once again
comes forward to defend, it pops up off the pad
nudged with the turn fine down leg
sharp turn, some bounce, going down leg, turned to square leg
goes back, this one arrives quicker than he thought, he punches, extra cover fails to stop it
punches a fullish delivery to the bowler off the back foot
on the front foot to block a tossed up ball
goes forward again, can't get the single, as the ball rolls to extra cover
same line outside off on the fullish delivery, defended off the front foot
whips this away but finds midwicket
pushed back to the bowler
comes down the track, Narine shortens it, it spins in and hits the pad
this bounced outside off, but Rohit played it well, making some room and running it past slip
lunges forward and plays it out with the spin to midwicket
hurries into middle and leg at 98 kph, turned to square leg
full and angled in, flicked past square leg
tossed up full, he reaches out and pats it back
flatter outside off, he steers it, but there is short third in place
whips a good length offspinner straight to midwicket
on the front foot and guides it to point for a single
flashes a drive to mid off, and hurries down for the run, throw misses, he would have just made it had it hit
this full delivery takes a leading edge and runs towards third man, they take on the throw and Rohit makes it back for the second
DK stretches forward as Sammy hits a good length outside off immediately
pushed to mid off
he walks out, Sammy bangs it in short, DK whacks it through midwicket and beats the fielder running to his left in the deep
pushed to extra cover
just outside off, good length, he pushes wide of cover for one
punched off the front foot to extra cover
eases a tossed up ball off the front foot to long on
comes forward to smother a tossed up ball

Samuels breaks the partnership, soft dismissal, Karthik pushed at a tossed up ball, it spun in, took the inner part of the bat and popped back to the bowler, replays show bat brushed pad first before it came down on the ball
leaves this one turning away from him outside off
quick and full, he is forward to defend
pushed back to the bowler
widish delivery steered to third man
the length is short, Raina is across and is off strike with a single to midwicket
a low full toss now, pushed out to the sweeper
short of a length, not bouncing too much, Raina expected it to do more, adjusted to jab it to deep square leg
that was wide, but fast, 141.8 kph, and zipped through even as Rohit tried to steer it

Rohit is still reining himself in against the pitched up deliveries, of course, all the wickets won't have helped, the shot was on, but he's eased it past the non-striker, though there is a long on in place, mid off has enough time to run across and stop it
punched back to the bowler off the back foot
on leg stump but he finds square leg as he works it away
Samuels not giving anything away, ths spins in to middle and is played out to midwicket
pushed down to long on
tossed up and spinning away appreciably, superb delivery, just around off stump, Raina follows the line and edges it, but it goes on the bounce to slip, just fell short
a wiser Raina lets this go outside off now
top edged swat over square leg but Rohit will take the couple for a half-century, he's dug in today, this has not been an easy pitch and attack to deal with
and he tries to guide one bouncing too close to him and is beaten
forces this to extra cover, didn't time it, went too hard at it
pitched up on the pads and he works it out to deep square
short ball from Sammy as well to Raina, 125.9 kph, down the leg side, pulled to fine leg
pitched up to the stumps and eased to long on
down the track and chipped it high over midwicket for a couple as long on runs around
106 kph dart pushed to cover
fires in another one on a good length, played out to midwicket
an attempted sweep for the first time, top edge flies over the keeper
pushed from around off stump to the sweeper
deft, waits and steers it late from close to off stump but finds short third
he went for it, first ball of the over from Sammy and Raina swings hard at a length ball, fortunately for him, it goes just over extra cover
swats the short ball into the ground to deep square leg
now Rohit, they have decided to get a move on, Rohit makes lots of room outside leg and slices this length ball from just outside off over point
takes a step outside leg, Sammy bowls it on the stumps, Rohit drills it down to long off
overpitched ball outside off eased to the sweeper

aarghh would be apt response to this brain fade from Rohit, after grinding it out for nearly 15 overs he swings at a pitched up delivery and the mishit sails tamely down to long off, when you have already got a couple of fours in the over ... sigh is an apt sign off
left alone outside off
steered to backward point
reaches out and pushes to sweeper cover
stretches forward and plays it out to midwicket
back and across and pushes to the off side
fuller, he nudges it to square leg off the front foot
gets width and chops it past backward point, third man runs around to field
goes across and pushes a length ball to extra cover off the back foot
on the pads, worked wide of midwicket, Pollard picks it up and lets go towards the keeper on the run, but the single is already taken
forward to push to long off for one more
flashed wide of point from the crease
width on the length ball and Raina punches to the sweeper
thick inside edge to short fine leg as Raina looks to defend from the crease
turned to square leg
lunges forward this time and pushes to the bowler
opens the face to one around off and runs it to point
left alone outside off
fullish length, 92.5 kph, Raina forward to defend, Samuels doing an outstanding job
worked in front of square leg off the pad
Raina moving forward nicely, now he gets to the pitch and drives to the left of the sweeper
flummoxed by the slower one, wanted to work it to square leg, misses and takes it on the body
thick outside edge as Raina reaches out to a widish one, away to point
pushes a length ball from the crease to extra cover
ended up driving over the line of this wide length ball which went to the keeper on the bounce
comes forward and turns an offspinner to midwicket from middle
tight line on off stump, punched back
nudges a fuller one past square leg
quick and right on middle, defended off the front foot
spins away outside off, steered to point
bounces outside off at 93 kph, but Raina remains in the crease and adjusts to guide this past slip
into the pads from a length, turned behind square leg
overpitched delivery driven down to long off
wide and overpitched slower one, Dhoni reaches out to go after it, and slices it high over covers
this was off the middle, flashed the cut hard but straight to point
slower one into the pad, away to fine leg
Raina gets the boundary, another wide and full one, he stretches to slap it in the air over backward point
offspinner bounces on middle, turned behind square leg
worked towards midwicket
Dhoni races across for the single after a soft push in front of cover
Raina dabs this sharply spinning delivery too close to slip and Gayle is able to get down and stop it
pushed to point
chopped towards point for a single
144.4 kph delivery but down the leg side
overpitched and on the pads but Raina cannot place it wide enough of fine leg
slow from back of a length, chopped behind point
just short of good length, he moves across and turns it off middle and leg to deep square
flicks an overpitched ball in the air wide of midwicket
again on the pads, 138.2 kph, Raina manages a single to deep square
slower length ball, Dhoni tries to guide it behind backward point but cannot beat the fielder
pats this offspinner in front of cover and takes off but Ramdin is after the ball and Dhoni has to get back
now Raina wants the single as Dhoni nudges in the air to midwicket but still no single coming
almost a yorker on middle and leg, Dhoni stabs it down to long on
whoa, that took off and spun across Raina, who belatedly dropped his wrists
pushed towards point
straighter and fuller one, Dhoni squeezes it to off
a bouncer but it is down leg
on the pads and sent down to fine leg
pitched up, Dhoni drives but does not time it, takes the single to mid off
Raina hops expecting the short one, it is not that short, pushes it towards point
another single taken off a length ball with a soft push in front of extra cover
moves across and pushes a back of a length ball to extra cover
shuffles around to off stump and nudges a length ball to midwicket
went searching for this tossed up ball, it spun away outside off to beat him
on the pads from a good length and tucked to deep square
nudges a quick and full one off the pad behind square for a sharp single, no trouble at all for Raina as he sprints through
he's got this away, made room outside leg, Narine bowled it quick on leg stump, Raina was able to guide it late past short third man
pushes an offspinner out to the sweeper
drills an overpitched ball wide of long off
stays around the crease and squeezes an incoming length ball to extra cover
shuffling across to far and missing the nudge as Roach sends it down leg from short of a good length
length ball on middle driven through midwicket

dropped, very tough chance, Roach almost takes Dhoni out with the offcutter, Dhoni goes for the big drive, a hand comes off the bat as the ball does not come on, Sammy runs back from point, dives, gets hands to it, but cannot hold on
leading edge to a back of a length ball and Dhoni charges down for the single
and Raina falls immediately after Dhoni's injury break, a short ball outside off, he goes for a tame cut and edges it through, bangs the bat into the ground on his way back
lunges forward and manages to squeeze a full ball past point's dive, Dhoni hobbles through, even hops in between, how long can he go on?
pushes at a tossed up ball and is beaten by the slight turn
beaten by flight and turn again outside off, lovely stuff
bounces outside off from a good length, cut to the sweeper
stretches forward and strikes it down to long on
hit through midwicket, Dhoni hobbles across again
full delivery pushed to extra cover
too quick for him, 141 kph, good length, going across, he tries to open the face but is beaten
lots of bounce, 141.1 kph, Jadeja goes on his toes and opens the face again, cannot connect
tries to swing this one off the pad, misses, it pops up towards point
out of nowhere, Jadeja responds by bashing an overpitched delivery between the bowler and Dhoni
misses the work of the pad, ball rolls to the keeper, there is a direct hit at the non-striker's and poor Dhoni has to hobble more for the ricochet
punches a length offspinner to extra cover
spinning into the body, shortish, Dhoni pulls hard and into the fine leg rope
fuller, he guides it to covers for a single
steered but finds short third man
cuts but finds backward point
worked away off the pad but finds square leg
Best takes out Dhoni, 141.6 kph inswinging full delivery, Dhoni tries to smoke it down the ground, misses, and loses his leg stump, Tino is pumped up, even more, that is
back of a length, Ashwin is across to defend it back
another inswinger, full and around off, Ashwin digs it out towards the lone slip
full and way down leg, Jadeja misses, Tino appeals loudly, he is dead sure about this one, but instead a wide is called
Jadeja gets a 144 kph chest-high snorter, he weaves away and tries to play it, gloves it away
a slower back of a length ball, moving away a tad, Ashwin tries running it to third man and misses
short of a length and into the body, Ashwin can only push it towards midwicket
full ball on leg, worked to short fine
walks outside off and nudges an offspinner to square leg
Jadeja steps out, mishits a flighted ball completely, and lands it precisely between three fielders, square leg, deep midwicket, and long on
not that short, but he's gone right back, bent the knee and pulled it over square leg, smart shot
hit to the sweeper for a single
Ashwin sets himself up for the reverse sweep, does not attempt the shot as this ball spins well down leg, keeper cannot collect it, Ashwin not getting the wide
Jadeja almost two-thirds up as Ashwin underedges a pull, midwicket runs forward but his throw is weak and misses
steered to third man
swings hard at a pacy short ball and misses
sends the slower one a long way down the leg side
Jadeja goes, opens up and swings at a length ball, it moves away a bit, takes the underedge and hits the stumps
short and into the body right away, 142 kph, defended off the back foot
Best ends fast, short and effective after a nightmare start in the morning, Bhuvneshwar swings and misses at a bouncer
beaten on the forward push, it spins in sharply through bat and pad, and also beats the keeper
flight and turn, a thick inside edge to midwicket as he pushes awkwardly
goes back to a tossed up ball and pushes to cover
overpitched straighter one on middle and off, Bhuvneshwar goes through with quick hands, and sends it high over mid off
almost another maximum, Bhuvneshwar shows superb timing as he lofts again over mid off, one bounce and over

inn2.comm: swinging away after starting just outside leg, good length, Gayle defends
swings it in this time but it starts down leg
hits the pads just outside leg and pops up towards point
drives a pitched up ball smoothly to mid off
too straight on a good length on off and Gayle has beaten wide mid off with a firm push this time
on the pads now and it is tucked to fine leg
attempts a loose waft at a wide delivery and is beaten
a short ball first up, 132.3 kph, and Gayle puts it away without fuss over square leg
an appeal for lbw, but the short of a length ball hit him high above the knee roll in front of leg, replays show that pitched outside leg too
Gayle pierces a good length ball through the covers
slight inswing takes this 137 kph delivery down the leg side
they get the big man, there was a short cover in place and Gayle's forced a back of a length ball to Raina there, he's a sharp fielder, Raina, and this is a sharp take
shuffles across outside off and defends a 138.6 kph length ball
pushes a pitched up ball from the crease to extra cover
comes forward to defend a straightish length ball around off
takes a step out and calmly smothers a good length ball
he gets going early this time Charles, gets half forward and smacks a length ball in the air just past the bowler
boom! bit of width on the length ball and he's whacked it past a diving mid off
third on the trot, a slower leg cutter on off, Charles can't be bothered, he's smeared it past mid on this time
bounces from a good length, keeper can't collect cleanly after Charles leaves

that looks close, umpire Gould gives it after a long appeal from Umesh, pitched up inswinger, beats the bat, hits pad, could it have been doing too much? Pitching on and hitting leg stump, says ball tracker
nice delivery, full and curling away, left alone
DK dives to his left with springs on his feet to take this down the leg side
drives a pitched up ball, midwicket runs across and parries it away
opens the face and defends a good length ball to point
one more goes, now Samuels jumps across to off, and plays on to a good length delivery which bounces extra on him
lets a length ball leave him with the angle close to off
right on off and middle, played out from the crease
nice leave, not far from off and straightening, but he is quite confident
good length ball defended to extra cover
lets another one go outside off
dead-bats another good length ball on off stump with a forward stride
pushes hard at a 140 kph pitched up delivery, it comes in a bit, and is in the air for a while but well short of mid on
appeal for caught behind, DK very sure, it held its line just outside off stump, but there wasn't a sound
pushed to mid on
sharp bouncer, 143.3 kph, Charles tries to half-heartedly swat it behind square, is too late
lets a 141.6 kph short ball go outside off stump
swings in a bit, hits the pad outside leg and rolls behind square
question asked for lbw, but this struck him too high from back of a length
good length ball guided to point
around off stump, he defends it to extra cover
Bhuvneshwar has shortened his length slightly to Charles, and is punched to extra cover
he bowled it fuller, and wider too, Charles needs no more invitation and drills it through the covers, with little backlift and little fuss
goes after a full and widish one, thick edge along the ground to deep backward point
biff! Charles is unrecognisable from the man who played against Sri Lanka, picks this length ball from outside off and mows it to the wide long on rope
there was a sound as this passed the batsman down leg, there is an appeal from the keeper for caught behind, but umpire Gould calls it wide, replays show it brushed the pad
short ball now, not much bite on it, Charles continues to score only in boundaries, as he pulls in front of square
Umesh gets this one on a length on off stump, Charles dead-bats it in his unique fashion
comes on the front foot to keep out another one on off
pitches it further up, Charles is slightly late in getting forward, but defends safely
pushes a pitched up ball on leg to midwicket
drives an overpitched ball, beats extra cover, but mid off gets around
whoa, this took off from a length, and moved away too, beat bat by a long way
outside edge, just short and to Ashwin's left at wide slip, Charles pushing half forward at a nippy length ball
allows one to go past with the angle outside off
goes hard at the drive but hasn;t timed it well enough to beat mid off running to his right
overpitched, again his drive finds wide mid off
tight line close to off stump, he lets it go
pitched up on middle, Bravo opens up and defends to the bowler
bouncer climbs, Bravo ducks and Karthik jumps to take it
good length ball ending on off, defended
plays off the back foot and pushes a length ball to covers
close to off stump first up, defended off the front foot
tossed up ball drifts in a tad, driven to long off
knocks back a full ball to the bowler
overpitched, some way outside off, Bravo smashes it over the bowler
plays it out square on off, slips runs in and prevents the single
spinning in to the pads, worked fine, Ashwin lumbers across, slows down, is slower to bend down one-handed, and lets it slip through
sharp start, bouncy back of a length ball at 145 kph, Charles plays with a weak angled bat and misses
into the pads now, and running away fine, the substitute Vijay runs across from fine leg and dives to save the boundary
defends a short of a length ball towards point
strays into the pads again and is picked to fine leg
shuffles to off and defends a short of a length ball into the pitch
plays out a length ball on the stumps to point
pats a length ball on off to the bowler
turns it off leg stump behind square
bit of width and Bravo flashes it through backward point, Ishant runs from third man, goes sprawling and parries the ball to the sweeper
length ball on off played out to extra cover
overpitched ball crunched through extra cover, he'd tried that a few times before but not found the gap, this time he does, powerful hit
